      "acceptanceCriteria": "Justification provided for continuum linear-elastic titanium alloy constitutive model and frictional contact formulation at screw–rod interface. Sensitivity analysis confirms QoI insensitivity to friction coefficient in range 0.15–0.35.",
      "rationale": "Ti-6Al-4V modeled as isotropic linear-elastic (E = 114 GPa, ν = 0.34) consistent with ASTM F1717 loading regime (pre-yield). Frictional contact (μ = 0.25 ± 0.10) at set-screw/rod interface: sensitivity analysis shows < 2% QoI variation across friction range. Model form consistent with published literature and FDA guidance. Required level 3 achieved."
