      "rationale": "N = 11 non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw constructs from two production lots tested across two independent laboratories (FDA CDRH biomechanics lab and DePuy Synthes testing facility). CMM dimensional verification confirms all constructs within drawing tolerances. Required level 3 achieved."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Test conditions span at least two load levels or two environmental conditions relevant to COU; test fixtures calibrated and traceable to NIST standards.",
      "rationale": "ASTM F1717 protocol applied at a single loading rate (5 mm/min) and ambient temperature. Only one test condition evaluated; multi-condition testing was outside project scope. Load cell and displacement transducer calibrated and NIST-traceable. Achieved level 2 is below required level 3 — this is the identified credibility gap. Mitigated by large sample size and inter-laboratory consistency."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
