      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoIs (stiffness, yield force, force at 40 mm displacement) are directly linked to the COU decision; mechanistic justification provided for each QoI's relevance to clinical performance.",
      "rationale": "Construct stiffness governs load transfer to vertebral bone; yield force is the primary safety threshold; force at 40 mm characterizes post-yield ductility relevant to fatigue life. All three QoIs are standard ASTM F1717 outputs and directly address the submission decision. Required level 3 achieved."
