    "rationale": "Twelve of thirteen V&V 40 credibility factors meet or exceed required levels. The single shortfall (Test conditions, achieved 2 vs required 3) is mitigated by inter-laboratory consistency across N=11 constructs and is documented as an accepted risk. All three QoIs satisfy E/uval < 1.96. The assessment team, drawing on the methodological framework described in the referenced comparative validation study (doi:10.1016/j.ymeth.2024.03.003), concludes that the FEA modeling framework is sufficiently credible for the stated COU. Decision: Accepted.",
